  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Besides stable chairs, sometimes neckrests or pillows are used to further fixate participants or increase their comfort (e.g., Trojano et al., 2012; Sprenger et al., 2013; Choe et al., 2016).",
    "We know of a further interesting solution to stimulate participants to sit still.",
    "Although they did not report it in the paper, Holleman et al. (2023) had children (8-10 years olds) wear a vest with Velcro attached to the back and to the backrest of the chair.",
    "Using this method, children felt resistance on their back when they moved, encouraging them to sit still.",
    "For younger participants (infants and toddlers), setups using car seats have been developed with the aim to afford them as little movement as possible (see, e.g., Hessels & Hooge, 2019, Figure 2 and associated text for an in-depth discussion)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Besides stable chairs, sometimes neckrests or pillows are used to further fixate participants or increase their comfort (e.g., Trojano et al., 2012; Sprenger et al., 2013; Choe et al., 2016).",
